<TITLE> Govt bars AC use in peak hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 30 (bdnews24.com)The government has barred use of air conditioners during peak hours from 6pm to 11pm daily until further notice for all residences, private and public offices, businesses and shopswith hospitals, restaurants and hotels exempt. The Bangladesh Energy Regulatory Commission in a circular issued Tuesday also said that AC temperature regulators cannot be lowered to less than 25 degrees Centigrade during off-peak hours. It instructed relevant authorities and persons to take required steps immediately and stated that the order is in force from now until further notice. The BERC order stated that the order was issued under Section 22 (a) and (m) of the Energy Act 2003, to face the energy shortage, ensure uninterrupted power supply to farmers for irrigation and reduce difficulties of Higher Secondary Certification examinees.
